Rules for the AI Agent
MUST Follow:

One Responsibility Per Type: Each struct/interface should have ONE clear job
No Circular Dependencies: Enforce strict layering - presentation depends on business logic, never the reverse
Immutable Results: Once created, results should never be modified
Interface Boundaries: Use interfaces between layers (e.g., cache.Manager not *cache.Cache)
Context Propagation: Pass context.Context through all concurrent operations
Error Wrapping: Always wrap errors with context using fmt.Errorf("doing X: %w", err)

Code Style Rules:

Package Names: Keep them short and clear (runner, not toolrunner)
Method Names: Verbs for actions (Run, Process), nouns for getters (Summary, Results)
Concurrency: Use errgroup for concurrent operations, channels only when necessary
Comments: Document WHY, not WHAT - explain the business logic

Migration Strategy:

Start with new packages - Don't modify existing code initially
Build interfaces first - Define contracts before implementations
Incremental replacement - Replace processor methods one at a time
Keep backward compatibility - Don't break existing CLI commands

